item.title: 天選者：第二季官方預告片 第二季官方預告片
item.description:
你已經看過《天選之人》了嗎？如果是的話，你最常見的問題是，"第二季什麼時候出？" 或者在很多情況下，它並不是一個問題，它更像是，"現在就給我第二季！" 好了，等待已經結束了。在美國東部時間復活節週日晚上8點（重要細節如下），第二季將在這裏推出一個巨大的全球直播。
還沒看過《天選者》？不要看這個預告片! 我們鼓勵你趕快追上第一季，因爲我們不能保證數百萬觀看第二季的人不會透露劇透。所以停止你正在做的事情，去 "狂歡耶穌"，正如我們喜歡說的那樣。
"我怎麼看《天選者》？" 問得好 它是免費的，很容易。是的，免費......甚至不需要電子郵件地址。查找 "天選之人"，無論你在哪裏得到你的手機應用程序，下載它，然後你可以自由和容易地連接它直接從那裏到你的流媒體設備（蘋果電視，火棍，Roku，Chromecast）。沒有流媒體設備？可能是時候買一個了。
"等等，免費又簡單？這怎麼可能？" 同樣，好問題。我們恰好是有史以來衆籌金額最高的媒體項目，這意味着我們完全是在系統之外完成的。我們建立了自己的應用程序，我們賣出了自己的DVD，而且我們不需要付費觀看，而是爲你提供了 "向前支付 "的機會，這樣我們就可以繼續保持免費，也可以製作未來的季節。但你不必這樣做。認真的。
我們的節目在世界每個國家都有收看，我們的節目被翻譯成50多種語言，我們聽到數以百萬計的人說，認識真實的耶穌改變了他們的生活。
第二季將於美國東部時間復活節週日晚上8:00開始，在我們的FB和Youtube頻道以及 "天選之人 "應用程序上進行全球直播，從那時起，它將永遠存在。
歡迎來到 "天選者"。習慣於與衆不同。

item.content:encoded:
Have you already seen The Chosen? If so, your most common question has been, "When is Season Two coming out?" Or in many cases, it hasn't been a question, it's been more like, "GIVE ME SEASON TWO NOW!" Well, the wait is over. Launching with a huge global livestream Easter Sunday at 8pm ET (important details below), Season Two is here.
Haven't seen The Chosen? Don't watch this trailer! We encourage you to catch up on Season One fast, because we can't promise the millions who will watch Season Two won't reveal spoilers. So stop what you're doing and go "binge Jesus," as we like to say.
"How do I watch The Chosen?" Good question. It's free and easy. Yes, free...doesn't even require an email address. Look up "The Chosen" wherever you get your phone apps, download it, and then you can freely and easily connect it directly from there to your streaming device (Apple TV, Firestick, Roku, Chromecast). Don't have a streaming device? Probably time to get one.
"Wait, free and easy? How is that possible?" Again, good question. We happen to be the #1 highest crowd-funded media project of all time, which means we've done this completely outside the system. We built our own app, we've sold our own DVDs, and instead of requiring payment to watch, we offer you the chance to "pay it forward" so we can continue to keep it free and also produce future seasons. But you don't have to. Seriously.
We're watched in literally every country in the world, we've been translated into over 50 languages, and we've heard from literally millions of people that getting to know the authentic Jesus has changed their life.
Season Two launches Easter Sunday, 8:00pm ET, with a huge global livestream on our FB & Youtube channels and "The Chosen" app, and from then on, it'll be available forever.
Welcome to The Chosen. Get used to different.

item.title: 同步化的祕密

item.title: 星際飛船｜SN11｜高空飛行試驗
item.description:
早在3月30日週二，SpaceX團隊就將嘗試對星際飛船序列號11（SN11）進行高空飛行試驗--這是我們在德克薩斯州星際基地對星際飛船原型進行的第四次高空飛行試驗。與之前的 "星艦 "高空飛行試驗類似，SN11將由三臺 "猛禽 "發動機提供動力完成上升，每臺發動機在飛行器到達遠地點--約10公里高度之前依次關閉。SN11將進行推進劑過渡到內部的頭艙，頭艙內存放着着陸推進劑，然後再調整方向，進行再入和受控的空氣動力下降。
星艦原型機將在主動空氣動力控制下下降，通過飛行器上的兩個前襟翼和兩個後襟翼的獨立運動來完成。所有四片襟翼均由機載飛行計算機驅動，以控制 "星艦 "在飛行過程中的姿態，並實現在預定地點的精確降落。SN11的 "猛禽 "發動機將在飛行器嘗試降落翻轉動作時重新點火，然後立即降落在發射架附近的着陸臺上。
受控的帶體襟翼的氣動下降和垂直着陸能力，加上空間內補給，對於將 "星際飛船 "降落到太陽系內不存在準備好的地面或跑道的目的地，並返回地球至關重要。這種能力將使一個完全可重複使用的運輸系統成爲可能，該系統旨在攜帶乘員和貨物進行長時間的星際飛行，並幫助人類返回月球，並前往火星及其他地方。
鑑於開發測試的動態時間表，請關注我們的社交媒體渠道，瞭解最新情況，我們將迎來SpaceX的第四次星際飛船高空飛行測試!
item.content:encoded:
As early as Tuesday, March 30, the SpaceX team will attempt a high-altitude flight test of Starship serial number 11 (SN11) – our fourth high-altitude flight test of a Starship prototype from Starbase in Texas. Similar to previous high-altitude flight tests of Starship, SN11 will be powered through ascent by three Raptor engines, each shutting down in sequence prior to the vehicle reaching apogee – approximately 10 km in altitude. SN11 will perform a propellant transition to the internal header tanks, which hold landing propellant, before reorienting itself for reentry and a controlled aerodynamic descent.
The Starship prototype will descend under active aerodynamic control, accomplished by independent movement of two forward and two aft flaps on the vehicle. All four flaps are actuated by an onboard flight computer to control Starship’s attitude during flight and enable precise landing at the intended location. SN11’s Raptor engines will then reignite as the vehicle attempts a landing flip maneuver immediately before touching down on the landing pad adjacent to the launch mount.
A controlled aerodynamic descent with body flaps and vertical landing capability, combined with in-space refilling, are critical to landing Starship at destinations across the solar system where prepared surfaces or runways do not exist, and returning to Earth. This capability will enable a fully reusable transportation system designed to carry both crew and cargo on long-duration, interplanetary flights and help humanity return to the Moon, and travel to Mars and beyond.
Given the dynamic schedule of development testing, stay tuned to our social media channels for updates as we move toward SpaceX’s fourth high-altitude flight test of Starship!

埃及蘇伊士運河的運營商表示，技術或人爲錯誤可能導致一艘大型集裝箱船擱淺。工程師們正在晝夜不停地工作，以重新浮起 "Ever Given "號。在過去的五天裏，這艘船一直堵塞着世界上最繁忙的航道之一。運河管理局主席希望在未來數天內進行挖泥工作，以解救這艘船。 Ever Given號，有史以來最大的集裝箱船之一，怎麼會堵在世界最繁忙的航道上？它又會在那裏停留多久呢？蘇伊士運河管理局主席面臨的問題比他能回答的還要多。但他說，造成這次事故的不僅僅是強風。 但在專家們進一步調查的同時，這艘船還得被解救出來。船頭周圍的2萬噸沙子已經被清除，9000噸壓艙水也被抽出，以減輕船隻的重量。到目前爲止，這項行動還沒有成功--但還有兩艘拖船正在趕來。如果他們不能移動它，下一步將是卸貨。 德國保險集團安聯稱，這一堵塞事件每週給全球經濟造成60億至100億美元的損失。全球十分之一的商船使用運河。

item.content:encoded:
The operators of Egypt's Suez Canal say technical or human error could have caused a huge container ship to run aground. Engineers are working round the clock to refloat the Ever Given. The vessel has been blocking one of the world's busiest shipping lanes for the last five days. The chairman of the canal authority hopes a dredging operation will free the ship in the next few days. How did the Ever Given, one of the biggest container ships ever built, end up blocking one of the world’s busiest shipping lanes? And how long will it stay there? The chairman of the Suez Canal Authority is facing more questions than he can answer. But he says more than just strong winds caused the accident. But while experts investigate further, the ship still has to be freed. 20,000 ton of sand have been removed from the area around the bow, and 9,000 tons of ballast water have been pumped out, in order to lighten the vessel. The operation has so far been unsuccessful - but two more tugs are on their way. If they can't move it, the next step will be to unload the cargo. The German insurance group Allianz says the blockage is costing the global economy between 6 and 10 billion dollars a week. A tenth of the world's merchant shipping uses the canal.
